# flow-server pinned-release checksums — the integrity source of truth for bin/flow-server-mcp.
# One line per published release asset: "<64-hex-sha256>  flow-server-<triple>[.exe]".
#
# BOOTSTRAP WINDOW (roadmap #39): bin/RELEASE was bumped to flow-server-v0.2.2 (the web-UI-removed,
# MCP-stdio-only core) but the v0.2.2 GitHub Release has not been published yet, so no checksums are
# committed below. While this file carries no asset line for a platform, the launcher resolves the
# binary by building from source (dev/CI) and smoke-pinned.sh + verify-prereqs §P cleanly SKIP/PASS
# the bootstrap window. Once the v0.2.2 release assets are published, paste their checksum lines here
# (one per platform: x86_64/aarch64 × linux-gnu/apple-darwin, plus x86_64-pc-windows-msvc.exe) to
# re-arm the deterministic pinned-binary path.
#
# To adopt a new release: bump Cargo.toml, cut the tag, publish the assets, then replace these lines
# + bin/RELEASE.
